        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="826" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d826">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Executive Secretariat Files: NSC 41 Folder</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a Conversation With
                        President Truman</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-16">September 16,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>This morning at the Cabinet meeting the President had in his hand a copy of NSC
                    41 which was the paper approved last February on trade with China. The President
                    said he thought it was out of date and should be revised. I assured him that the
                    matter would be looked into at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>D[<hi rend="smallcaps">ean</hi>] A[<hi rend="smallcaps">cheson</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
